00:00:10.120 --> 00:00:10.990
recreational mathematics --

00:00:10.990 --> 00:00:16.120
everyone loves perfect numbers -- the smallest perfect number is six. [The] reason we call it a perfect number is because

00:00:16.120 --> 00:00:18.820
it equals the sum of its proper factors.

00:00:18.900 --> 00:00:25.140
So 6 is divisible by 1, is divisible by 2, it's divisible by 3, also divisible by 6?

00:00:25.510 --> 00:00:27.899
So I could put six on this list,

00:00:28.420 --> 00:00:32.009
but proper factors mean numbers that go into a number

00:00:32.020 --> 00:00:37.400
but aren't the number itself -- in fact, we can remove six from the list and six equals one plus

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:43.620
two plus three, [this] equals the sum of its proper factors. The next number which this works for is 28,

00:00:44.280 --> 00:00:48.600
because that equals one plus two plus four plus seven plus

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:55.940
14, which are all of its -- all those proper factors summed together give you that number. You could -- some people

00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:58.030
like to say,

00:00:58.030 --> 00:01:03.390
perfect numbers are equal to -- like all of their factors equal twice [the number].

00:01:03.729 --> 00:01:11.099
So if I did -- if I was super pedant, and instead of using proper factors I used all the factors, that would give me 56,

00:01:11.100 --> 00:01:14.850
which is twice because we are just adding the number on the end right, so yeah, same thing.

00:01:14.850 --> 00:01:19.379
I just -- I ignore that, and just stick with the proper factors. The next one Brady is?

