23 or something. And so

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:21.330
people look at that

00:04:21.330 --> 00:04:26.480
and go: "well that must be prime", because they see this pattern and think it must work -- doesn't hold, doesn't work for 11 in fact

00:04:26.540 --> 00:04:28.680
well, the next one it works for is not 12 because that's

00:04:28.800 --> 00:04:35.100
4095, which we know is out of here, the next one is 13, which is

00:04:35.240 --> 00:04:43.560
8191, that is prime, that one works, and so, in fact, that pattern, when people spot these prime values of N,

00:04:44.330 --> 00:04:46.330
giving these numbers prime,

00:04:46.940 --> 00:04:50.559
Only works in one direction as such okay?

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:56.740
Let me -- let me be very clear with this -- one way we could describe this pattern is, if n is prime,

00:04:57.040 --> 00:05:02.580
then 2 to the n minus 1 is prime as well, but that doesn't work,

00:05:02.590 --> 00:05:08.799
we just proved that. But we haven't disproved the reverse, and the reverse of a statement is different, so for example

00:05:08.810 --> 00:05:10.810
I could say all --

00:05:11.180 --> 00:05:13.180
all girls can wear hats.

00:05:13.759 --> 00:05:16.149
Logical statement, you're a girl, you can wear a hat, right?

00:05:16.150 --> 00:05:20.650
But I can't then say, if you can wear a hat, you must be a girl, right,

00:05:20.650 --> 00:05:23.650
it doesn't go the other way, right, because you know... (scrambling for words)

00:05:24.889 --> 00:05:27.098
Well the ability to wear a hat is necessary,

00:05:27.099 --> 00:05:30.549
but not sufficient to be a girl, anyway, the point is, right, the reverse is a different story,

00:05:30.549 --> 00:05:33.240
and in this case the reverse is true -- if

00:05:33.320 --> 00:05:36.720
2 to the n minus 1 is prime, then n

00:05:36.729 --> 00:05:42.279
must have been prime. So the backwards still [holds], which is why it will still only be the primes, it just won't be all of them.

